  "prompt": "How do I report a bug/loophole on Quora? What will I get for that?",
  "response": "To report a bug or loophole on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Quora Help Center**: Go to the Quora Help Center by clicking on the 'Help' option at the bottom of the page or directly visiting [help.quora.com](https://help.quora.com).\n\n2. **Submit a Request**: Look for an option to submit a request or report an issue. This is usually found in the Help Center under the \"Contact Us\" section.\n\n3. **Fill out the Form**: Provide all necessary details about the bug or loophole you\u2019ve found. Be as specific as possible, including steps to reproduce the issue, any relevant screenshots, and your device/browser information.\n\n4. **Provide Your Contact Information**: If there\u2019s an option to leave your email or other contact information, include it so the Quora team can reach you for follow-up.\n\n5. **Send Your Report**: Submit the form and wait for a response from the Quora team.\n\n### Possible Rewards\nQuora does not typically offer monetary rewards for reporting bugs. However, reporting bugs can contribute to a better user experience on the platform, and you might receive acknowledgment, a thank-you note, or even a badge for your contribution, depending on the specific circumstance.\n\nIf you are concerned about the severity of the loophole, it's always best to report it responsibly and directly to the platform to ensure it is addressed appropriately.",
